**Segments**

- By Type: Epoxy Resins, Polyester Resins, Polyurethane Resins, Others
- By Application: Motors & Generators, Home Appliances, Transformers, Automotive Components, Others
- By End-Use Industry: Electrical & Electronics, Automotive, Aerospace, Industrial, Others

Impregnating resins are crucial components in various industries as they enhance the electrical insulation properties of materials, prevent moisture ingress, and offer thermal stability. In terms of type segmentation, epoxy resins are anticipated to witness significant growth due to their excellent adhesion properties, high mechanical strength, and chemical resistance. Polyester resins are also expected to have a substantial market share as they are cost-effective and offer good dielectric properties. The polyurethane resins segment is projected to grow steadily owing to their flexibility and high-temperature resistance. In the application segment, the motors & generators category is likely to dominate the market due to the increasing demand for energy-efficient electrical equipment. The home appliances segment is also expected to grow as impregnating resins enhance the durability and performance of appliances. Within the end-use industry segment, the electrical & electronics sector is projected to lead the market, driven by advancements in electronics manufacturing and the increasing need for reliable insulation materials.

